{"TopicId":116978,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Mission Lines fade at innapropriate POV","CreatedByName":"boolybooly","CreatedById":6572,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-27T14:40:15Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"boolybooly","CreatedById":6572,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-27T14:40:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI made a little video to show you how when plotting a satellite mission intercept, the mission target orbit line seen as red here fades to abscurity at precisely the wrong moment, ie when you zoom in close to make a fine adjustment the line vanishes from view. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe line needs to remain visible, and btw this is true of all orbit lines as far as I can see and they should never fade. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/YjfaYs_MVNE?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E \u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/YjfaYs_MVNE?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHow are you supposed to embed videos here these days?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https: